So that's great for a nice interactive experience where you

00:35:01.159 --> 00:35:05.159
Don't have to really program to start interacting with a model.

00:35:05.159 --> 00:35:09.159
But once you kind of go from that to actually trying to build

00:35:09.159 --> 00:35:13.159
Something programmatically with the llm, the first one you're

00:35:13.159 --> 00:35:17.159
Probably going to want to reach for is this chat method.

00:35:17.159 --> 00:35:21.159
So i can submit some string input, and this is basically the

00:35:21.159 --> 00:35:25.159
Same as submitting through the chat web interface.

00:35:25.159 --> 00:35:28.159
The main difference here is, you know, i'm going to be

00:35:28.159 --> 00:35:32.159
Running this at the console on the lower left-hand side, and

00:35:32.159 --> 00:35:36.159
The nice thing about the chat method is it basically kind of

00:35:36.159 --> 00:35:40.159
Assumes you're in an interactive setting, you're at the console,

